shine
------------------------------------------
shine is a blazing fast mp3 encoding library implemented in fixed-point
arithmetic.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.3-1
  cygwin-devel-3.6.3-1
  libshine-devel-3.1.1-1bl2
  libshine3-3.1.1-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.4.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.44-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/toots/shine

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/toots/shine/archive/refs/tags/3.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack shine-3.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./shine-3.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/shine-3.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/shine-3.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libshine3-3.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libshine-devel-3.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(shine)
  /usr/bin/shineenc.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/shine.README
  /usr/share/doc/shine/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/shine/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/shine/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/shine/README.old

(libshine3)
  /usr/bin/cygshine-3.dll

(libshine-devel)
  /usr/include/shine/layer3.h
  /usr/lib/libshine.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/shine.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

